{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775863731108,"sessionID":"ses_286465c60ffepIiYZc6Y4bIElI","part":{"id":"prt_d79ba0ef1001N3odvDflo0patL","messageID":"msg_d79ba0150001J23b5fk3e1LRW6","sessionID":"ses_286465c60ffepIiYZc6Y4bIElI","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_521cced991d94bf7bae37dac","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Specification вҖ” AR-015: PicoD Command Execution API\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: **Module:** `pkg/picod`  \n6: **Language:** Go  \n7: **Size:** M  \n8: **Type:** New feature вҖ” Secure command execution API with resource limits and sandboxing\n9: \n10: ---\n11: \n12: ## Requirements & Scenarios\n13: \n14: ### REQ-001: PicoD Struct and Initialization\n15: \n16: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide a `PicoD` struct representing a command execution sandbox with fields: `sandboxID`, `workDir`, `limits`, `securityOpts`, `logger`. The system SHALL provide functional options: `WithWorkDir`, `WithLimits`, `WithSecurityOpts`, `WithLogger`. The system SHALL provide `New(sandboxID string, opts ...Option) *PicoD` constructor.\n17: \n18: #### Scenario: New creates PicoD with defaults\n19: - **GIVEN** a sandbox ID `\"sandbox-123\"`\n20: - **WHEN** `New(\"sandbox-123\")` is called with no options\n21: - **THEN** the returned `*PicoD` has `sandboxID = \"sandbox-123\"`, `workDir` from `PICOD_WORKDIR` env (default `/tmp/picod`), `limits` from `DefaultResourceLimits()`, `securityOpts` from `DefaultSecurityOpts()`, `logger` is nil\n22: \n23: #### Scenario: WithWorkDir sets working directory\n24: - **GIVEN** a directory path `\"/custom/workdir\"`\n25: - **WHEN** `New(\"sandbox-123\", WithWorkDir(\"/custom/workdir\"))` is called\n26: - **THEN** the returned `*PicoD` has `workDir = \"/custom/workdir\"`\n27: \n28: #### Scenario: WithLimits sets resource limits\n29: - **GIVEN** a `*ResourceLimits` with `Timeout = 60s`\n30: - **WHEN** `New(\"sandbox-123\", WithLimits(limits))` is called\n31: - **THEN** the returned `*PicoD` has `limits` set to the provided value\n32: \n33: #### Scenario: WithSecurityOpts sets security options\n34: - **GIVEN** a `*SecurityOptions` with `UID = 1000`\n35: - **WHEN** `New(\"sandbox-123\", WithSecurityOpts(opts))` is called\n36: - **THEN** the returned `*PicoD` has `securityOpts` set to the provided value\n37: \n38: #### Scenario: WithLogger sets logger\n39: - **GIVEN** a `klog.Logger` instance\n40: - **WHEN** `New(\"sandbox-123\", WithLogger(logger))` is called\n41: - **THEN** the returned `*PicoD` has `logger` set to the provided value\n42: \n43: ---\n44: \n45: ### REQ-002: Resource Limits Configuration\n46: \n47: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide a `ResourceLimits` struct with fields: `Timeout` (time.Duration), `MaxCPU` (float64), `MaxMemory` (int64, bytes), `MaxOutputSize` (int64, bytes), `MaxProcesses` (int). The system SHALL provide `DefaultResourceLimits() *ResourceLimits` returning defaults from environment variables. The system SHALL provide `(l *ResourceLimits) Validate() error`.\n48: \n49: #### Scenario: DefaultResourceLimits returns defaults\n50: - **GIVEN** no environment variables set\n51: - **WHEN** `DefaultResourceLimits()` is called\n52: - **THEN** returns `*ResourceLimits` with `Timeout = 30s`, `MaxCPU = 1.0`, `MaxMemory = 128Mi`, `MaxOutputSize = 10MB`, `MaxProcesses = 10`\n53: \n54: #### Scenario: DefaultResourceLimits uses environment variables\n55: - **GIVEN** `PICOD_DEFAULT_TIMEOUT=60s`, `PICOD_MAX_MEMORY=256Mi`, `PICOD_MAX_CPU=2.0`, `PICOD_MAX_OUTPUT_SIZE=20MB`, `PICOD_MAX_PROCESSES=20`\n56: - **WHEN** `DefaultResourceLimits()` is called\n57: - **THEN** returns `*ResourceLimits` with values parsed from environment\n58: \n59: #### Scenario: Validate accepts valid limits\n60: - **GIVEN** `ResourceLimits{Timeout: 30s, MaxCPU: 1.0, MaxMemory: 134217728, MaxOutputSize: 10485760, MaxProcesses: 10}`\n61: - **WHEN** `Validate()` is called\n62: - **THEN** returns nil (no error)\n63: \n64: #### Scenario: Validate rejects zero timeout\n65: - **GIVEN** `ResourceLimits{Timeout: 0}`\n66: - **WHEN** `Validate()` is called\n67: - **THEN** returns error indicating Timeout is required\n68: \n69: #### Scenario: Validate rejects negative CPU\n70: - **GIVEN** `ResourceLimits{MaxCPU: -0.5}`\n71: - **WHEN** `Validate()` is called\n72: - **THEN** returns error indicating MaxCPU must be positive\n73: \n74: #### Scenario: Validate rejects negative memory\n75: - **GIVEN** `ResourceLimits{MaxMemory: -100}`\n76: - **WHEN** `Validate()` is called\n77: - **THEN** returns error indicating MaxMemory must be positive\n78: \n79: #### Scenario: Validate rejects zero output size\n80: - **GIVEN** `ResourceLimits{MaxOutputSize: 0}`\n81: - **WHEN** `Validate()` is called\n82: - **THEN** returns error indicating MaxOutputSize is required\n83: \n84: #### Scenario: Validate rejects zero max processes\n85: - **GIVEN** `ResourceLimits{MaxProcesses: 0}`\n86: - **WHEN** `Validate()` is called\n87: - **THEN** returns error indicating MaxProcesses is required\n88: \n89: ---\n90: \n91: ### REQ-003: Security Options Configuration\n92: \n93: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide a `SecurityOptions` struct with fields: `UID` (int), `GID` (int), `Capabilities` ([]string), `ReadOnlyFS` (bool), `NoNetwork` (bool), `AllowedCommands` ([]string). The system SHALL provide `DefaultSecurityOpts() *SecurityOptions`. The system SHALL provide `(o *SecurityOptions) Validate() error`.\n94: \n95: #### Scenario: DefaultSecurityOpts returns defaults\n96: - **GIVEN** no special configuration\n97: - **WHEN** `DefaultSecurityOpts()` is called\n98: - **THEN** returns `*SecurityOptions` with `UID = -1` (unchanged), `GID = -1`, `Capabilities = nil`, `ReadOnlyFS = false`, `NoNetwork = false`, `AllowedCommands = nil`\n99: \n100: #### Scenario: Validate accepts valid options\n101: - **GIVEN** `SecurityOptions{UID: 1000, GID: 1000}`\n102: - **WHEN** `Validate()` is called\n103: - **THEN** returns nil (no error)\n104: \n105: #### Scenario: Validate rejects negative UID (except -1)\n106: - **GIVEN** `SecurityOptions{UID: -5}`\n107: - **WHEN** `Validate()` is called\n108: - **THEN** returns error indicating UID must be >= -1\n109: \n110: #### Scenario: Validate rejects negative GID (except -1)\n111: - **GIVEN** `SecurityOptions{GID: -5}`\n112: - **WHEN** `Validate()` is called\n113: - **THEN** returns error indicating GID must be >= -1\n114: \n115: #### Scenario: Validate accepts -1 UID (unchanged)\n116: - **GIVEN** `SecurityOptions{UID: -1}`\n117: - **WHEN** `Validate()` is called\n118: - **THEN** returns nil (no error, indicates no UID change)\n119: \n120: ---\n121: \n122: ### REQ-004: Command Structure\n123: \n124: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide a `Command` struct with fields: `Path` (string), `Args` ([]string), `Env` ([]string), `Dir` (string), `Stdin` (io.Reader), `Stdout` (io.Writer), `Stderr` (io.Writer). If `Stdout` or `Stderr` is nil, output SHALL be captured internally.\n125: \n126: #### Scenario: Command with all fields\n127: - **GIVEN** a command with `Path = \"/bin/echo\"`, `Args = []string{\"echo\", \"hello\"}`, `Env = []string{\"FOO=bar\"}`\n128: - **WHEN** the command is executed\n129: - **THEN** the command runs with specified path, args, and environment\n130: \n131: #### Scenario: Command with nil stdout captures output\n132: - **GIVEN** a command with `Stdout = nil`\n133: - **WHEN** the command is executed\n134: - **THEN** stdout is captured in `CommandResult.Stdout`\n135: \n136: #### Scenario: Command with custom stdout uses provided writer\n137: - **GIVEN** a command with `Stdout = &bytes.Buffer{}`\n138: - **WHEN** the command is executed\n139: - **THEN** stdout is written to the provided buffer\n140: \n141: ---\n142: \n143: ### REQ-005: CommandResult Structure\n144: \n145: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide a `CommandResult` struct with fields: `ExitCode` (int), `Stdout` ([]byte), `Stderr` ([]byte), `Duration` (time.Duration), `OOMKilled` (bool), `Timeout` (bool).\n146: \n147: #### Scenario: Successful command result\n148: - **GIVEN** a command that exits with code 0\n149: - **WHEN** the command completes\n150: - **THEN** `CommandResult` has `ExitCode = 0`, `Stdout` contains output, `Timeout = false`, `OOMKilled = false`\n151: \n152: #### Scenario: Failed command result\n153: - **GIVEN** a command that exits with code 1\n154: - **WHEN** the command completes\n155: - **THEN** `CommandResult` has `ExitCode = 1`, `Stderr` contains error output\n156: \n157: #### Scenario: Timeout result\n158: - **GIVEN** a command that exceeds timeout\n159: - **WHEN** the command is terminated\n160: - **THEN** `CommandResult` has `Timeout = true`, `ExitCode = -1` (or appropriate signal code)\n161: \n162: #### Scenario: OOM killed result\n163: - **GIVEN** a command that exceeds memory limit\n164: - **WHEN** the command is killed\n165: - **THEN** `CommandResult` has `OOMKilled = true`, `ExitCode` indicates signal\n166: \n167: ---\n168: \n169: ### REQ-006: Run Method\n170: \n171: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide `(p *PicoD) Run(ctx context.Context, cmd *Command) (*CommandResult, error)`. The method SHALL execute the command, wait for completion, apply resource limits, capture output, and return result. The method SHALL respect context cancellation.\n172: \n173: #### Scenario: Run executes simple command\n174: - **GIVEN** a PicoD instance and `Command{Path: \"/bin/echo\", Args: []string{\"echo\", \"hello\"}}`\n175: - **WHEN** `Run(ctx, cmd)` is called\n176: - **THEN** command executes, returns `*CommandResult` with `Stdout = []byte(\"hello\\n\")`, `ExitCode = 0`\n177: \n178: #### Scenario: Run captures stderr\n179: - **GIVEN** a command that writes to stderr (`/bin/ls /nonexistent`)\n180: - **WHEN** `Run(ctx, cmd)` is called\n181: - **THEN** `CommandResult.Stderr` contains error message, `ExitCode != 0`\n182: \n183: #### Scenario: Run respects context cancellation\n184: - **GIVEN** a long-running command and a context that is cancelled after 1s\n185: - **WHEN** `Run(ctx, cmd)` is called\n186: - **THEN** command is terminated, returns error with type `ExecutionErrorCancelled`\n187: \n188: #### Scenario: Run enforces timeout\n189: - **GIVEN** a command and `limits.Timeout = 5s`, command takes 10s\n190: - **WHEN** `Run(ctx, cmd)` is called\n191: - **THEN** command is terminated after 5s, returns error with type `ExecutionErrorTimeout`\n192: \n193: #### Scenario: Run returns nil error on success\n194: - **GIVEN** a valid command that completes successfully\n195: - **WHEN** `Run(ctx, cmd)` is called\n196: - **THEN** error is nil\n197: \n198: ---\n199: \n200: ### REQ-007: Start Method and Process Management\n201: \n202: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide `(p *PicoD) Start(ctx context.Context, cmd *Command) (*Process, error)`. The system SHALL provide a `Process` struct with fields: `PID` (int), methods `Wait() (*CommandResult, error)` and `Kill(signal os.Signal) error`.\n203: \n204: #### Scenario: Start launches background process\n205: - **GIVEN** a PicoD instance and a long-running command\n206: - **WHEN** `Start(ctx, cmd)` is called\n207: - **THEN** returns `*Process` with `PID > 0`, command runs in background\n208: \n209: #### Scenario: Process.Wait waits for completion\n210: - **GIVEN** a `*Process` from `Start()`\n211: - **WHEN** `process.Wait()` is called\n212: - **THEN** blocks until command completes, returns `*CommandResult`\n213: \n214: #### Scenario: Process.Kill terminates process\n215: - **GIVEN** a running `*Process`\n216: - **WHEN** `process.Kill(os.Kill)` is called\n217: - **THEN** process is terminated, subsequent `Wait()` returns error\n218: \n219: #### Scenario: Process.Kill with SIGTERM\n220: - **GIVEN** a running `*Process`\n221: - **WHEN** `process.Kill(syscall.SIGTERM)` is called\n222: - **THEN** process receives SIGTERM and can handle gracefully\n223: \n224: ---\n225: \n226: ### REQ-008: Output Streaming\n227: \n228: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide an `OutputHandler` interface with methods: `OnStdout(data []byte)`, `OnStderr(data []byte)`, `OnComplete(result *CommandResult)`. The system SHALL provide `(p *PicoD) RunWithStreaming(ctx context.Context, cmd *Command, handler OutputHandler) (*CommandResult, error)`.\n229: \n230: #### Scenario: RunWithStreaming streams stdout\n231: - **GIVEN** a command that produces output and an `OutputHandler` implementation\n232: - **WHEN** `RunWithStreaming(ctx, cmd, handler)` is called\n233: - **THEN** `OnStdout` is called incrementally as output is produced\n234: \n235: #### Scenario: RunWithStreaming streams stderr\n236: - **GIVEN** a command that writes to stderr\n237: - **WHEN** `RunWithStreaming(ctx, cmd, handler)` is called\n238: - **THEN** `OnStderr` is called with error output\n239: \n240: #### Scenario: RunWithStreaming calls OnComplete\n241: - **GIVEN** a command that completes\n242: - **WHEN** `RunWithStreaming(ctx, cmd, handler)` completes\n243: - **THEN** `OnComplete(result)` is called with final result\n244: \n245: #### Scenario: RunWithStreaming respects output size limit\n246: - **GIVEN** a command producing output exceeding `MaxOutputSize`\n247: - **WHEN** `RunWithStreaming(ctx, cmd, handler)` is called\n248: - **THEN** streaming stops at limit, returns error with type `ExecutionErrorResource`\n249: \n250: ---\n251: \n252: ### REQ-009: Command Validation\n253: \n254: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide `ValidateCommand(cmd *Command, opts *SecurityOptions) error`. The system SHALL provide `IsPathSafe(path, workDir string) bool`. Commands SHALL be validated before execution.\n255: \n256: #### Scenario: ValidateCommand accepts valid command\n257: - **GIVEN** a command with absolute path within workDir\n258: - **WHEN** `ValidateCommand(cmd, opts)` is called\n259: - **THEN** returns nil (no error)\n260: \n261: #### Scenario: ValidateCommand rejects path traversal\n262: - **GIVEN** a command with `Path = \"../../../etc/passwd\"`\n263: - **WHEN** `ValidateCommand(cmd, opts)` is called\n264: - **THEN** returns error with type `ExecutionErrorSecurity`\n265: \n266: #### Scenario: IsPathSafe returns true for safe path\n267: - **GIVEN** `path = \"/workspace/subdir/file.txt\"`, `workDir = \"/workspace\"`\n268: - **WHEN** `IsPathSafe(path, workDir)` is called\n269: - **THEN** returns true\n270: \n271: #### Scenario: IsPathSafe returns false for path traversal\n272: - **GIVEN** `path = \"/workspace/../etc/passwd\"`, `workDir = \"/workspace\"`\n273: - **WHEN** `IsPathSafe(path, workDir)` is called\n274: - **THEN** returns false\n275: \n276: #### Scenario: ValidateCommand enforces allowlist\n277: - **GIVEN** `SecurityOptions{AllowedCommands: []string{\"/bin/echo\"}}` and `Command{Path: \"/bin/ls\"}`\n278: - **WHEN** `ValidateCommand(cmd, opts)` is called\n279: - **THEN** returns error with type `ExecutionErrorSecurity`\n280: \n281: ---\n282: \n283: ### REQ-010: Privilege Dropping\n284: \n285: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide `DropPrivileges(uid, gid int) error`. When `UID`/`GID` are set in `SecurityOptions`, the system SHALL drop privileges before executing commands.\n286: \n287: #### Scenario: DropPrivileges changes UID/GID\n288: - **GIVEN** running as root, `uid = 1000`, `gid = 1000`\n289: - **WHEN** `DropPrivileges(1000, 1000)` is called\n290: - **THEN** process runs with specified UID/GID\n291: \n292: #### Scenario: DropPrivileges fails when not root\n293: - **GIVEN** running as non-root user\n294: - **WHEN** `DropPrivileges(0, 0)` is called (trying to become root)\n295: - **THEN** returns error (operation not permitted)\n296: \n297: ---\n298: \n299: ### REQ-011: Resource Limit Enforcement\n300: \n301: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide `SetResourceLimits(limits *ResourceLimits) error`. The system SHALL enforce CPU, memory, and process limits using OS primitives (setrlimit, cgroups, or platform-specific APIs).\n302: \n303: #### Scenario: SetResourceLimits sets memory limit\n304: - **GIVEN** `ResourceLimits{MaxMemory: 134217728}`\n305: - **WHEN** `SetResourceLimits(limits)` is called\n306: - **THEN** process memory is limited to 128Mi (via setrlimit or cgroup)\n307: \n308: #### Scenario: SetResourceLimits sets process limit\n309: - **GIVEN** `ResourceLimits{MaxProcesses: 5}`\n310: - **WHEN** `SetResourceLimits(limits)` is called\n311: - **THEN** process cannot spawn more than 5 child processes\n312: \n313: #### Scenario: Memory limit enforced\n314: - **GIVEN** a command with `MaxMemory = 10Mi` that tries to allocate 20Mi\n315: - **WHEN** command executes\n316: - **THEN** process is killed, `CommandResult.OOMKilled = true`\n317: \n318: ---\n319: \n320: ### REQ-012: ExecutionError Types\n321: \n322: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide `ExecutionError` struct with fields: `Type` (ExecutionErrorType), `Message` (string), `Underlying` (error). The system SHALL define error types: `ExecutionErrorTimeout`, `ExecutionErrorOOM`, `ExecutionErrorCancelled`, `ExecutionErrorSecurity`, `ExecutionErrorResource`, `ExecutionErrorExec`.\n323: \n324: #### Scenario: Timeout error type\n325: - **GIVEN** a command that times out\n326: - **WHEN** error is returned\n327: - **THEN** error type is `ExecutionErrorTimeout`\n328: \n329: #### Scenario: OOM error type\n330: - **GIVEN** a command that exceeds memory limit\n331: - **WHEN** error is returned\n332: - **THEN** error type is `ExecutionErrorOOM`\n333: \n334: #### Scenario: Cancelled error type\n335: - **GIVEN** a cancelled context\n336: - **WHEN** `Run(ctx, cmd)` returns error\n337: - **THEN** error type is `ExecutionErrorCancelled`\n338: \n339: #### Scenario: Security error type\n340: - **GIVEN** a command failing security validation\n341: - **WHEN** error is returned\n342: - **THEN** error type is `ExecutionErrorSecurity`\n343: \n344: #### Scenario: Exec error type\n345: - **GIVEN** a command with non-existent path\n346: - **WHEN** `Run(ctx, cmd)` is called\n347: - **THEN** error type is `ExecutionErrorExec`\n348: \n349: ---\n350: \n351: ### REQ-013: Environment Variables\n352: \n353: **Requirement:** The system SHALL support environment variables for configuration: `PICOD_WORKDIR`, `PICOD_DEFAULT_TIMEOUT`, `PICOD_MAX_MEMORY`, `PICOD_MAX_CPU`, `PICOD_MAX_OUTPUT_SIZE`, `PICOD_MAX_PROCESSES`.\n354: \n355: #### Scenario: PICOD_WORKDIR sets default workdir\n356: - **GIVEN** `PICOD_WORKDIR=/custom/picod`\n357: - **WHEN** `New(\"sandbox-123\")` is called without `WithWorkDir`\n358: - **THEN** `PicoD.workDir = \"/custom/picod\"`\n359: \n360: #### Scenario: PICOD_DEFAULT_TIMEOUT sets timeout\n361: - **GIVEN** `PICOD_DEFAULT_TIMEOUT=120s`\n362: - **WHEN** `DefaultResourceLimits()` is called\n363: - **THEN** `ResourceLimits.Timeout = 120s`\n364: \n365: #### Scenario: PICOD_MAX_MEMORY with unit suffix\n366: - **GIVEN** `PICOD_MAX_MEMORY=512Mi`\n367: - **WHEN** `DefaultResourceLimits()` is called\n368: - **THEN** `ResourceLimits.MaxMemory = 536870912` (512 * 1024 * 1024)\n369: \n370: #### Scenario: PICOD_MAX_CPU accepts float\n371: - **GIVEN** `PICOD_MAX_CPU=0.5`\n372: - **WHEN** `DefaultResourceLimits()` is called\n373: - **THEN** `ResourceLimits.MaxCPU = 0.5`\n374: \n375: #### Scenario: Default values when env not set\n376: - **GIVEN** no `PICOD_*` environment variables set\n377: - **WHEN** `DefaultResourceLimits()` is called\n378: - **THEN** returns hardcoded defaults (30s timeout, 1.0 CPU, 128Mi memory, 10MB output, 10 processes)\n379: \n380: ---\n381: \n382: ### REQ-014: Logging\n383: \n384: **Requirement:** The system SHALL use `klog.Logger` for structured logging. The system SHALL log command start, completion, timeout, cancellation, and errors.\n385: \n386: #### Scenario: Run logs command start\n387: - **GIVEN** a PicoD instance with a logger\n388: - **WHEN** `Run(ctx, cmd)` is called\n389: - **THEN** log entry contains \"command_start\", command path, sandbox ID\n390: \n391: #### Scenario: Run logs command completion\n392: - **GIVEN** a command that completes\n393: - **WHEN** `Run(ctx, cmd)` completes\n394: - **THEN** log entry contains \"command_complete\", exit code, duration\n395: \n396: #### Scenario: Run logs timeout\n397: - **GIVEN** a command that times out\n398: - **WHEN** `Run(ctx, cmd)` times out\n399: - **THEN** log entry contains \"command_timeout\", duration, command path\n400: \n401: ---\n402: \n403: ### REQ-015: File Structure\n404: \n405: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide files: `pkg/picod/picod.go` (PicoD struct, New, options), `pkg/picod/limits.go` (ResourceLimits), `pkg/picod/security.go` (SecurityOptions, validation), `pkg/picod/executor.go` (Run, Start, Process), `pkg/picod/output.go` (OutputHandler, streaming), `pkg/picod/errors.go` (ExecutionError types).\n406: \n407: #### Scenario: Package structure\n408: - **GIVEN** the `pkg/picod` package\n409: - **WHEN** compiled\n410: - **THEN** all required files are present and export required types/functions\n411: \n412: ---\n413: \n414: ## Data Types\n415: \n416: ```go\n417: // PicoD represents a command execution sandbox\n418: type PicoD struct {\n419:     sandboxID    string\n420:     workDir      string\n421:     limits       *ResourceLimits\n422:     securityOpts *SecurityOptions\n423:     logger       klog.Logger\n424: }\n425: \n426: // ResourceLimits defines execution resource limits\n427: type ResourceLimits struct {\n428:     Timeout       time.Duration\n429:     MaxCPU        float64\n430:     MaxMemory     int64\n431:     MaxOutputSize int64\n432:     MaxProcesses  int\n433: }\n434: \n435: // SecurityOptions defines security settings\n436: type SecurityOptions struct {\n437:     UID             int\n438:     GID             int\n439:     Capabilities    []string\n440:     ReadOnlyFS      bool\n441:     NoNetwork       bool\n442:     AllowedCommands []string\n443: }\n444: \n445: // Command represents a command to execute\n446: type Command struct {\n447:     Path   string\n448:     Args   []string\n449:     Env    []string\n450:     Dir    string\n451:     Stdin  io.Reader\n452:     Stdout io.Writer\n453:     Stderr io.Writer\n454: }\n455: \n456: // CommandResult represents execution result\n457: type CommandResult struct {\n458:     ExitCode  int\n459:     Stdout    []byte\n460:     Stderr    []byte\n461:     Duration  time.Duration\n462:     OOMKilled bool\n463:     Timeout   bool\n464: }\n465: \n466: // Process represents a running process\n467: type Process struct {\n468:     PID int\n469: }\n470: \n471: // ExecutionError represents an execution error\n472: type ExecutionError struct {\n473:     Type       ExecutionErrorType\n474:     Message    string\n475:     Underlying error\n476: }\n477: \n478: type ExecutionErrorType string\n479: \n480: const (\n481:     ExecutionErrorTimeout   ExecutionErrorType = \"timeout\"\n482:     ExecutionErrorOOM       ExecutionErrorType = \"oom\"\n483:     ExecutionErrorCancelled ExecutionErrorType = \"cancelled\"\n484:     ExecutionErrorSecurity  ExecutionErrorType = \"security\"\n485:     ExecutionErrorResource  ExecutionErrorType = \"resource\"\n486:     ExecutionErrorExec      ExecutionErrorType = \"exec\"\n487: )\n488: ```\n489: \n490: ---\n491: \n492: ## Environment Variables\n493: \n494: | Variable | Required | Default | Notes |\n495: |----------|----------|---------|-------|\n496: | `PICOD_WORKDIR` | No | `/tmp/picod` | Base working directory |\n497: | `PICOD_DEFAULT_TIMEOUT` | No | `30s` | Default command timeout |\n498: | `PICOD_MAX_MEMORY` | No | `128Mi` | Default memory limit |\n499: | `PICOD_MAX_CPU` | No | `1.0` | Default CPU limit |\n500: | `PICOD_MAX_OUTPUT_SIZE` | No | `10MB` | Default output size limit |\n501: | `PICOD_MAX_PROCESSES` | No | `10` | Default process limit |\n502: \n503: ---\n504: \n505: ## File Structure\n506: \n507: ```\n508: pkg/picod/\n509: в”ңв”Җв”Җ picod.go          # PicoD struct, New(), functional options\n510: в”ңв”Җв”Җ limits.go         # ResourceLimits, DefaultResourceLimits(), Validate()\n511: в”ңв”Җв”Җ security.go       # SecurityOptions, ValidateCommand(), IsPathSafe(), DropPrivileges()\n512: в”ңв”Җв”Җ executor.go       # Run(), Start(), Process, Command, CommandResult\n513: в”ңв”Җв”Җ output.go         # OutputHandler, RunWithStreaming()\n514: в”ңв”Җв”Җ errors.go         # ExecutionError, ExecutionErrorType\n515: в”ңв”Җв”Җ picod_test.go     # Unit tests\n516: в””в”Җв”Җ doc.go            # Package documentation\n517: ```\n518: \n519: ---\n520: \n521: ## Dependencies\n522: \n523: | Package | Purpose |\n524: |---------|---------|\n525: | `context` | Command cancellation and timeouts |\n526: | `os/exec` | Command execution primitives |\n527: | `syscall` | Process management, signals, setrlimit |\n528: | `k8s.io/klog/v2` | Structured logging |\n529: | `time` | Duration and timeout handling |\n530: | `io` | Stream interfaces |\n531: | `os` | File operations, process signals |\n532: \n533: ---\n534: \n535: ## Acceptance Checklist\n536: \n537: - [ ] `pkg/picod/picod.go` вҖ” PicoD struct, New(), functional options\n538: - [ ] `pkg/picod/limits.go` вҖ” ResourceLimits with Validate()\n539: - [ ] `pkg/picod/security.go` вҖ” SecurityOptions, validation functions\n540: - [ ] `pkg/picod/executor.go` вҖ” Run(), Start(), Process struct\n541: - [ ] `pkg/picod/output.go` вҖ” OutputHandler, RunWithStreaming()\n542: - [ ] `pkg/picod/errors.go` вҖ” ExecutionError types\n543: - [ ] `pkg/picod/picod_test.go` вҖ” Unit tests for all 15 requirements\n544: - [ ] All environment variables supported\n545: - [ ] Resource limits enforced (timeout, memory, CPU, processes)\n546: - [ ] Security validations prevent path traversal and unauthorized commands\n547: - [ ] Context cancellation supported\n548: - [ ] Streaming output supported\n549: - [ ] klog logging integrated\n550: - [ ] Code coverage >= 80%\n\n(End of file - total 550 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Specification вҖ” AR-015: PicoD Command Execution API\n\n## Overview\n\n**Module:** `pkg/picod`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** M  \n**Type:** New feature вҖ” Secure command execution API with resource limits and sandboxing\n\n---\n\n## Requirements & Scenarios\n\n### REQ-001: PicoD Struct and Initialization\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL provide a `PicoD` struct representing a command execution sandbox with fields: `sandboxID`, `workDir`, `limits`, `securityOpts`, `logger`. The system SHALL provide functional options: `WithWorkDir`, `WithLimits`, `WithSecurityOpts`, `WithLogger`. The system SHALL provide `New(sandboxID string, opts ...Option) *PicoD` constructor.\n\n#### Scenario: New creates PicoD with defaults\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox ID `\"sandbox-123\"`\n- **WHEN** `New(\"sandbox-123\")` is called with no options","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775863731087,"end":1775863731104}}}}
