{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775863740453,"sessionID":"ses_286465c60ffepIiYZc6Y4bIElI","part":{"id":"prt_d79ba2783001EpzNMFv1a0nlmc","messageID":"msg_d79ba13df001zmt351462wghRu","sessionID":"ses_286465c60ffepIiYZc6Y4bIElI","type":"tool","tool":"edit","callID":"toolu_ff2ab393db564d8aa5808226","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/delta-spec.md","oldString":"# Delta Specification вҖ” AR-015: PicoD Command Execution API\n\n## Overview\n\n**Module:** `pkg/picod`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** M  \n**Type:** New feature вҖ” Secure command execution API with resource limits and sandboxing\n\n---\n\n## Requirements & Scenarios","newString":"# Delta Specification вҖ” AR-019: CLI дәҢиҝӣеҲ¶е…ҘеҸЈ (4 binaries)\n\n## Overview\n\n**Module:** `cmd`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** M  \n**Type:** New feature вҖ” CLI binaries for agentcube Kubernetes resources\n\n**Base Specs:** deployment/client-go.md\n\n---\n\n## Requirements & Scenarios"},"output":"Edit applied successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"diff":"Index: /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/delta-spec.md\n===================================================================\n--- /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/delta-spec.md\n+++ /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/delta-spec.md\n@@ -1,13 +1,15 @@\n-# Delta Specification вҖ” AR-015: PicoD Command Execution API\n+# Delta Specification вҖ” AR-019: CLI дәҢиҝӣеҲ¶е…ҘеҸЈ (4 binaries)\n \n ## Overview\n \n-**Module:** `pkg/picod`  \n+**Module:** `cmd`  \n **Language:** Go  \n **Size:** M  \n-**Type:** New feature вҖ” Secure command execution API with resource limits and sandboxing\n+**Type:** New feature вҖ” CLI binaries for agentcube Kubernetes resources\n \n+**Base Specs:** deployment/client-go.md\n+\n ---\n \n ## Requirements & Scenarios\n \n","filediff":{"file":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/delta-spec.md","before":"# Delta Specification вҖ” AR-015: PicoD Command Execution API\n\n## Overview\n\n**Module:** `pkg/picod`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** M  \n**Type:** New feature вҖ” Secure command execution API with resource limits and sandboxing\n\n---\n\n## Requirements & Scenarios\n\n### REQ-001: PicoD Struct and Initialization\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL provide a `PicoD` struct representing a command execution sandbox with fields: `sandboxID`, `workDir`, `limits`, `securityOpts`, `logger`. The system SHALL provide functional options: `WithWorkDir`, `WithLimits`, `WithSecurityOpts`, `WithLogger`. The system SHALL provide `New(sandboxID string, opts ...Option) *PicoD` constructor.\n\n#### Scenario: New creates PicoD with defaults\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox ID `\"sandbox-123\"`\n- **WHEN** `New(\"sandbox-123\")` is called with no options\n- **THEN** the returned `*PicoD` has `sandboxID = \"sandbox-123\"`, `workDir` from `PICOD_WORKDIR` env (default `/tmp/picod`), `limits` from `DefaultResourceLimits()`, `securityOpts` from `DefaultSecurityOpts()`, `logger` is nil\n\n#### Scenario: WithWorkDir sets working directory\n- **GIVEN** a directory path `\"/custom/workdir\"`\n- **WHEN** `New(\"sandbox-123\", WithWorkDir(\"/custom/workdir\"))` is called\n- **THEN** the returned `*PicoD` has `workDir = \"/custom/workdir\"`\n\n#### Scenario: WithLimits sets resource limits\n- **GIVEN** a `*ResourceLimits` with `Timeout = 60s`\n- **WHEN** `New(\"sandbox-123\", WithLimits(limits))` is called\n- **THEN** the returned `*PicoD` has `limits` set to the provided value\n\n#### Scenario: WithSecurityOpts sets security options\n- **GIVEN** a `*SecurityOptions` with `UID = 1000`\n- **WHEN** `New(\"sandbox-123\", WithSecurityOpts(opts))` is called\n- **THEN** the returned `*PicoD` has `securityOpts` set to the provided value\n\n#### Scenario: WithLogger sets logger\n- **GIVEN** a `klog.Logger` instance\n- **WHEN** `New(\"sandbox-123\", WithLogger(logger))` is called\n- **THEN** the returned `*PicoD` has `logger` set to the provided value\n\n---\n\n### REQ-002: Resource Limits Configuration\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL provide a `ResourceLimits` struct with fields: `Timeout` (time.Duration), `MaxCPU` (float64), `MaxMemory` (int64, bytes), `MaxOutputSize` (int64, bytes), `MaxProcesses` (int). The system SHALL provide `DefaultResourceLimits() *ResourceLimits` returning defaults from environment variables. The system SHALL provide `(l *ResourceLimits) Validate() error`.\n\n#### Scenario: DefaultResourceLimits returns defaults\n- **GIVEN** no environment variables set\n- **WHEN** `DefaultResourceLimits()` is called\n- **THEN** returns `*ResourceLimits` with `Timeout = 30s`, `MaxCPU = 1.0`, `MaxMemory = 128Mi`, `MaxOutputSize = 10MB`, `MaxProcesses = 10`\n\n#### Scenario: DefaultResourceLimits uses environment variables\n- **GIVEN** `PICOD_DEFAULT_TIMEOUT=60s`, `PICOD_MAX_MEMORY=256Mi`, `PICOD_MAX_CPU=2.0`, `PICOD_MAX_OUTPUT_SIZE=20MB`, `PICOD_MAX_PROCESSES=20`\n- **WHEN** `DefaultResourceLimits()` is called\n- **THEN** returns `*ResourceLimits` with values parsed from environment\n\n#### Scenario: Validate accepts valid limits\n- **GIVEN** `ResourceLimits{Timeout: 30s, MaxCPU: 1.0, MaxMemory: 134217728, MaxOutputSize: 10485760, MaxProcesses: 10}`\n- **WHEN** `Validate()` is called\n- **THEN** returns nil (no error)\n\n#### Scenario: Validate rejects zero timeout\n- **GIVEN** `ResourceLimits{Timeout: 0}`\n- **WHEN** `Validate()` is called\n- **THEN** returns error indicating Timeout is required\n\n#### Scenario: Validate rejects negative CPU\n- **GIVEN** `ResourceLimits{MaxCPU: -0.5}`\n- **WHEN** `Validate()` is called\n- **THEN** returns error indicating MaxCPU must be positive\n\n#### Scenario: Validate rejects negative memory\n- **GIVEN** `ResourceLimits{MaxMemory: -100}`\n- **WHEN** `Validate()` is called\n- **THEN** returns error indicating MaxMemory must be positive\n\n#### Scenario: Validate rejects zero output size\n- **GIVEN** `ResourceLimits{MaxOutputSize: 0}`\n- **WHEN** `Validate()` is called\n- **THEN** returns error indicating MaxOutputSize is required\n\n#### Scenario: Validate rejects zero max processes\n- **GIVEN** `ResourceLimits{MaxProcesses: 0}`\n- **WHEN** `Validate()` is called\n- **THEN** returns error indicating MaxProcesses is required\n\n---\n\n### REQ-003: Security Options Configuration\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL provide a `SecurityOptions` struct with fields: `UID` (int), `GID` (int), `Capabilities` ([]string), `ReadOnlyFS` (bool), `NoNetwork` (bool), `AllowedCommands` ([]string). The system SHALL provide `DefaultSecurityOpts() *SecurityOptions`. The system SHALL provide `(o *SecurityOptions) Validate() error`.\n\n#### Scenario: DefaultSecurityOpts returns defaults\n- **GIVEN** no special configuration\n- **WHEN** `DefaultSecurityOpts()` is called\n- **THEN** returns `*SecurityOptions` with `UID = -1` (unchanged), `GID = -1`, `Capabilities = nil`, `ReadOnlyFS = false`, `NoNetwork = false`, `AllowedCommands = nil`\n\n#### Scenario: Validate accepts valid options\n- **GIVEN** `SecurityOptions{UID: 1000, GID: 1000}`\n- **WHEN** `Validate()` is called\n- **THEN** returns nil (no error)\n\n#### Scenario: Validate rejects negative UID (except -1)\n- **GIVEN** `SecurityOptions{UID: -5}`\n- **WHEN** `Validate()` is called\n- **THEN** returns error indicating UID must be >= -1\n\n#### Scenario: Validate rejects negative GID (except -1)\n- **GIVEN** `SecurityOptions{GID: -5}`\n- **WHEN** `Validate()` is called\n- **THEN** returns error indicating GID must be >= -1\n\n#### Scenario: Validate accepts -1 UID (unchanged)\n- **GIVEN** `SecurityOptions{UID: -1}`\n- **WHEN** `Validate()` is called\n- **THEN** returns nil (no error, indicates no UID change)\n\n---\n\n### REQ-004: Command Structure\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL provide a `Command` struct with fields: `Path` (string), `Args` ([]string), `Env` ([]string), `Dir` (string), `Stdin` (io.Reader), `Stdout` (io.Writer), `Stderr` (io.Writer). If `Stdout` or `Stderr` is nil, output SHALL be captured internally.\n\n#### Scenario: Command with all fields\n- **GIVEN** a command with `Path = \"/bin/echo\"`, `Args = []string{\"echo\", \"hello\"}`, `Env = []string{\"FOO=bar\"}`\n- **WHEN** the command is executed\n- **THEN** the command runs with specified path, args, and environment\n\n#### Scenario: Command with nil stdout captures output\n- **GIVEN** a command with `Stdout = nil`\n- **WHEN** the command is executed\n- **THEN** stdout is captured in `CommandResult.Stdout`\n\n#### Scenario: Command with custom stdout uses provided writer\n- **GIVEN** a command with `Stdout = &bytes.Buffer{}`\n- **WHEN** the command is executed\n- **THEN** stdout is written to the provided buffer\n\n---\n\n### REQ-005: CommandResult Structure\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL provide a `CommandResult` struct with fields: `ExitCode` (int), `Stdout` ([]byte), `Stderr` ([]byte), `Duration` (time.Duration), `OOMKilled` (bool), `Timeout` (bool).\n\n#### Scenario: Successful command result\n- **GIVEN** a command that exits with code 0\n- **WHEN** the command completes\n- **THEN** `CommandResult` has `ExitCode = 0`, `Stdout` contains output, `Timeout = false`, `OOMKilled = false`\n\n#### Scenario: Failed command result\n- **GIVEN** a command that exits with code 1\n- **WHEN** the command completes\n- **THEN** `CommandResult` has `ExitCode = 1`, `Stderr` contains error output\n\n#### Scenario: Timeout result\n- **GIVEN** a command that exceeds timeout\n- **WHEN** the command is terminated\n- **THEN** `CommandResult` has `Timeout = true`, `ExitCode = -1` (or appropriate signal code)\n\n#### Scenario: OOM killed result\n- **GIVEN** a command that exceeds memory limit\n- **WHEN** the command is killed\n- **THEN** `CommandResult` has `OOMKilled = true`, `ExitCode` indicates signal\n\n---\n\n### REQ-006: Run Method\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL provide `(p *PicoD) Run(ctx context.Context, cmd *Command) (*CommandResult, error)`. The method SHALL execute the command, wait for completion, apply resource limits, capture output, and return result. The method SHALL respect context cancellation.\n\n#### Scenario: Run executes simple command\n- **GIVEN** a PicoD instance and `Command{Path: \"/bin/echo\", Args: []string{\"echo\", \"hello\"}}`\n- **WHEN** `Run(ctx, cmd)` is called\n- **THEN** command executes, returns `*CommandResult` with `Stdout = []byte(\"hello\\n\")`, `ExitCode = 0`\n\n#### Scenario: Run captures stderr\n- **GIVEN** a command that writes to stderr (`/bin/ls /nonexistent`)\n- **WHEN** `Run(ctx, cmd)` is called\n- **THEN** `CommandResult.Stderr` contains error message, `ExitCode != 0`\n\n#### Scenario: Run respects context cancellation\n- **GIVEN** a long-running command and a context that is cancelled after 1s\n- **WHEN** `Run(ctx, cmd)` is called\n- **THEN** command is terminated, returns error with type `ExecutionErrorCancelled`\n\n#### Scenario: Run enforces timeout\n- **GIVEN** a command and `limits.Timeout = 5s`, command takes 10s\n- **WHEN** `Run(ctx, cmd)` is called\n- **THEN** command is terminated after 5s, returns error with type `ExecutionErrorTimeout`\n\n#### Scenario: Run returns nil error on success\n- **GIVEN** a valid command that completes successfully\n- **WHEN** `Run(ctx, cmd)` is called\n- **THEN** error is nil\n\n---\n\n### REQ-007: Start Method and Process Management\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL provide `(p *PicoD) Start(ctx context.Context, cmd *Command) (*Process, error)`. The system SHALL provide a `Process` struct with fields: `PID` (int), methods `Wait() (*CommandResult, error)` and `Kill(signal os.Signal) error`.\n\n#### Scenario: Start launches background process\n- **GIVEN** a PicoD instance and a long-running command\n- **WHEN** `Start(ctx, cmd)` is called\n- **THEN** returns `*Process` with `PID > 0`, command runs in background\n\n#### Scenario: Process.Wait waits for completion\n- **GIVEN** a `*Process` from `Start()`\n- **WHEN** `process.Wait()` is called\n- **THEN** blocks until command completes, returns `*CommandResult`\n\n#### Scenario: Process.Kill terminates process\n- **GIVEN** a running `*Process`\n- **WHEN** `process.Kill(os.Kill)` is called\n- **THEN** process is terminated, subsequent `Wait()` returns error\n\n#### Scenario: Process.Kill with SIGTERM\n- **GIVEN** a running `*Process`\n- **WHEN** `process.Kill(syscall.SIGTERM)` is called\n- **THEN** process receives SIGTERM and can handle gracefully\n\n---\n\n### REQ-008: Output Streaming\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL provide an `OutputHandler` interface with methods: `OnStdout(data []byte)`, `OnStderr(data []byte)`, `OnComplete(result *CommandResult)`. The system SHALL provide `(p *PicoD) RunWithStreaming(ctx context.Context, cmd *Command, handler OutputHandler) (*CommandResult, error)`.\n\n#### Scenario: RunWithStreaming streams stdout\n- **GIVEN** a command that produces output and an `OutputHandler` implementation\n- **WHEN** `RunWithStreaming(ctx, cmd, handler)` is called\n- **THEN** `OnStdout` is called incrementally as output is produced\n\n#### Scenario: RunWithStreaming streams stderr\n- **GIVEN** a command that writes to stderr\n- **WHEN** `RunWithStreaming(ctx, cmd, handler)` is called\n- **THEN** `OnStderr` is called with error output\n\n#### Scenario: RunWithStreaming calls OnComplete\n- **GIVEN** a command that completes\n- **WHEN** `RunWithStreaming(ctx, cmd, handler)` completes\n- **THEN** `OnComplete(result)` is called with final result\n\n#### Scenario: RunWithStreaming respects output size limit\n- **GIVEN** a command producing output exceeding `MaxOutputSize`\n- **WHEN** `RunWithStreaming(ctx, cmd, handler)` is called\n- **THEN** streaming stops at limit, returns error with type `ExecutionErrorResource`\n\n---\n\n### REQ-009: Command Validation\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL provide `ValidateCommand(cmd *Command, opts *SecurityOptions) error`. The system SHALL provide `IsPathSafe(path, workDir string) bool`. Commands SHALL be validated before execution.\n\n#### Scenario: ValidateCommand accepts valid command\n- **GIVEN** a command with absolute path within workDir\n- **WHEN** `ValidateCommand(cmd, opts)` is called\n- **THEN** returns nil (no error)\n\n#### Scenario: ValidateCommand rejects path traversal\n- **GIVEN** a command with `Path = \"../../../etc/passwd\"`\n- **WHEN** `ValidateCommand(cmd, opts)` is called\n- **THEN** returns error with type `ExecutionErrorSecurity`\n\n#### Scenario: IsPathSafe returns true for safe path\n- **GIVEN** `path = \"/workspace/subdir/file.txt\"`, `workDir = \"/workspace\"`\n- **WHEN** `IsPathSafe(path, workDir)` is called\n- **THEN** returns true\n\n#### Scenario: IsPathSafe returns false for path traversal\n- **GIVEN** `path = \"/workspace/../etc/passwd\"`, `workDir = \"/workspace\"`\n- **WHEN** `IsPathSafe(path, workDir)` is called\n- **THEN** returns false\n\n#### Scenario: ValidateCommand enforces allowlist\n- **GIVEN** `SecurityOptions{AllowedCommands: []string{\"/bin/echo\"}}` and `Command{Path: \"/bin/ls\"}`\n- **WHEN** `ValidateCommand(cmd, opts)` is called\n- **THEN** returns error with type `ExecutionErrorSecurity`\n\n---\n\n### REQ-010: Privilege Dropping\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL provide `DropPrivileges(uid, gid int) error`. When `UID`/`GID` are set in `SecurityOptions`, the system SHALL drop privileges before executing commands.\n\n#### Scenario: DropPrivileges changes UID/GID\n- **GIVEN** running as root, `uid = 1000`, `gid = 1000`\n- **WHEN** `DropPrivileges(1000, 1000)` is called\n- **THEN** process runs with specified UID/GID\n\n#### Scenario: DropPrivileges fails when not root\n- **GIVEN** running as non-root user\n- **WHEN** `DropPrivileges(0, 0)` is called (trying to become root)\n- **THEN** returns error (operation not permitted)\n\n---\n\n### REQ-011: Resource Limit Enforcement\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL provide `SetResourceLimits(limits *ResourceLimits) error`. The system SHALL enforce CPU, memory, and process limits using OS primitives (setrlimit, cgroups, or platform-specific APIs).\n\n#### Scenario: SetResourceLimits sets memory limit\n- **GIVEN** `ResourceLimits{MaxMemory: 134217728}`\n- **WHEN** `SetResourceLimits(limits)` is called\n- **THEN** process memory is limited to 128Mi (via setrlimit or cgroup)\n\n#### Scenario: SetResourceLimits sets process limit\n- **GIVEN** `ResourceLimits{MaxProcesses: 5}`\n- **WHEN** `SetResourceLimits(limits)` is called\n- **THEN** process cannot spawn more than 5 child processes\n\n#### Scenario: Memory limit enforced\n- **GIVEN** a command with `MaxMemory = 10Mi` that tries to allocate 20Mi\n- **WHEN** command executes\n- **THEN** process is killed, `CommandResult.OOMKilled = true`\n\n---\n\n### REQ-012: ExecutionError Types\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL provide `ExecutionError` struct with fields: `Type` (ExecutionErrorType), `Message` (string), `Underlying` (error). The system SHALL define error types: `ExecutionErrorTimeout`, `ExecutionErrorOOM`, `ExecutionErrorCancelled`, `ExecutionErrorSecurity`, `ExecutionErrorResource`, `ExecutionErrorExec`.\n\n#### Scenario: Timeout error type\n- **GIVEN** a command that times out\n- **WHEN** error is returned\n- **THEN** error type is `ExecutionErrorTimeout`\n\n#### Scenario: OOM error type\n- **GIVEN** a command that exceeds memory limit\n- **WHEN** error is returned\n- **THEN** error type is `ExecutionErrorOOM`\n\n#### Scenario: Cancelled error type\n- **GIVEN** a cancelled context\n- **WHEN** `Run(ctx, cmd)` returns error\n- **THEN** error type is `ExecutionErrorCancelled`\n\n#### Scenario: Security error type\n- **GIVEN** a command failing security validation\n- **WHEN** error is returned\n- **THEN** error type is `ExecutionErrorSecurity`\n\n#### Scenario: Exec error type\n- **GIVEN** a command with non-existent path\n- **WHEN** `Run(ctx, cmd)` is called\n- **THEN** error type is `ExecutionErrorExec`\n\n---\n\n### REQ-013: Environment Variables\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL support environment variables for configuration: `PICOD_WORKDIR`, `PICOD_DEFAULT_TIMEOUT`, `PICOD_MAX_MEMORY`, `PICOD_MAX_CPU`, `PICOD_MAX_OUTPUT_SIZE`, `PICOD_MAX_PROCESSES`.\n\n#### Scenario: PICOD_WORKDIR sets default workdir\n- **GIVEN** `PICOD_WORKDIR=/custom/picod`\n- **WHEN** `New(\"sandbox-123\")` is called without `WithWorkDir`\n- **THEN** `PicoD.workDir = \"/custom/picod\"`\n\n#### Scenario: PICOD_DEFAULT_TIMEOUT sets timeout\n- **GIVEN** `PICOD_DEFAULT_TIMEOUT=120s`\n- **WHEN** `DefaultResourceLimits()` is called\n- **THEN** `ResourceLimits.Timeout = 120s`\n\n#### Scenario: PICOD_MAX_MEMORY with unit suffix\n- **GIVEN** `PICOD_MAX_MEMORY=512Mi`\n- **WHEN** `DefaultResourceLimits()` is called\n- **THEN** `ResourceLimits.MaxMemory = 536870912` (512 * 1024 * 1024)\n\n#### Scenario: PICOD_MAX_CPU accepts float\n- **GIVEN** `PICOD_MAX_CPU=0.5`\n- **WHEN** `DefaultResourceLimits()` is called\n- **THEN** `ResourceLimits.MaxCPU = 0.5`\n\n#### Scenario: Default values when env not set\n- **GIVEN** no `PICOD_*` environment variables set\n- **WHEN** `DefaultResourceLimits()` is called\n- **THEN** returns hardcoded defaults (30s timeout, 1.0 CPU, 128Mi memory, 10MB output, 10 processes)\n\n---\n\n### REQ-014: Logging\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL use `klog.Logger` for structured logging. The system SHALL log command start, completion, timeout, cancellation, and errors.\n\n#### Scenario: Run logs command start\n- **GIVEN** a PicoD instance with a logger\n- **WHEN** `Run(ctx, cmd)` is called\n- **THEN** log entry contains \"command_start\", command path, sandbox ID\n\n#### Scenario: Run logs command completion\n- **GIVEN** a command that completes\n- **WHEN** `Run(ctx, cmd)` completes\n- **THEN** log entry contains \"command_complete\", exit code, duration\n\n#### Scenario: Run logs timeout\n- **GIVEN** a command that times out\n- **WHEN** `Run(ctx, cmd)` times out\n- **THEN** log entry contains \"command_timeout\", duration, command path\n\n---\n\n### REQ-015: File Structure\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL provide files: `pkg/picod/picod.go` (PicoD struct, New, options), `pkg/picod/limits.go` (ResourceLimits), `pkg/picod/security.go` (SecurityOptions, validation), `pkg/picod/executor.go` (Run, Start, Process), `pkg/picod/output.go` (OutputHandler, streaming), `pkg/picod/errors.go` (ExecutionError types).\n\n#### Scenario: Package structure\n- **GIVEN** the `pkg/picod` package\n- **WHEN** compiled\n- **THEN** all required files are present and export required types/functions\n\n---\n\n## Data Types\n\n```go\n// PicoD represents a command execution sandbox\ntype PicoD struct {\n    sandboxID    string\n    workDir      string\n    limits       *ResourceLimits\n    securityOpts *SecurityOptions\n    logger       klog.Logger\n}\n\n// ResourceLimits defines execution resource limits\ntype ResourceLimits struct {\n    Timeout       time.Duration\n    MaxCPU        float64\n    MaxMemory     int64\n    MaxOutputSize int64\n    MaxProcesses  int\n}\n\n// SecurityOptions defines security settings\ntype SecurityOptions struct {\n    UID             int\n    GID             int\n    Capabilities    []string\n    ReadOnlyFS      bool\n    NoNetwork       bool\n    AllowedCommands []string\n}\n\n// Command represents a command to execute\ntype Command struct {\n    Path   string\n    Args   []string\n    Env    []string\n    Dir    string\n    Stdin  io.Reader\n    Stdout io.Writer\n    Stderr io.Writer\n}\n\n// CommandResult represents execution result\ntype CommandResult struct {\n    ExitCode  int\n    Stdout    []byte\n    Stderr    []byte\n    Duration  time.Duration\n    OOMKilled bool\n    Timeout   bool\n}\n\n// Process represents a running process\ntype Process struct {\n    PID int\n}\n\n// ExecutionError represents an execution error\ntype ExecutionError struct {\n    Type       ExecutionErrorType\n    Message    string\n    Underlying error\n}\n\ntype ExecutionErrorType string\n\nconst (\n    ExecutionErrorTimeout   ExecutionErrorType = \"timeout\"\n    ExecutionErrorOOM       ExecutionErrorType = \"oom\"\n    ExecutionErrorCancelled ExecutionErrorType = \"cancelled\"\n    ExecutionErrorSecurity  ExecutionErrorType = \"security\"\n    ExecutionErrorResource  ExecutionErrorType = \"resource\"\n    ExecutionErrorExec      ExecutionErrorType = \"exec\"\n)\n```\n\n---\n\n## Environment Variables\n\n| Variable | Required | Default | Notes |\n|----------|----------|---------|-------|\n| `PICOD_WORKDIR` | No | `/tmp/picod` | Base working directory |\n| `PICOD_DEFAULT_TIMEOUT` | No | `30s` | Default command timeout |\n| `PICOD_MAX_MEMORY` | No | `128Mi` | Default memory limit |\n| `PICOD_MAX_CPU` | No | `1.0` | Default CPU limit |\n| `PICOD_MAX_OUTPUT_SIZE` | No | `10MB` | Default output size limit |\n| `PICOD_MAX_PROCESSES` | No | `10` | Default process limit |\n\n---\n\n## File Structure\n\n```\npkg/picod/\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ picod.go          # PicoD struct, New(), functional options\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ limits.go         # ResourceLimits, DefaultResourceLimits(), Validate()\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ security.go       # SecurityOptions, ValidateCommand(), IsPathSafe(), DropPrivileges()\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ executor.go       # Run(), Start(), Process, Command, CommandResult\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ output.go         # OutputHandler, RunWithStreaming()\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ errors.go         # ExecutionError, ExecutionErrorType\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ picod_test.go     # Unit tests\nв””в”Җв”Җ doc.go            # Package documentation\n```\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n| Package | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|\n| `context` | Command cancellation and timeouts |\n| `os/exec` | Command execution primitives |\n| `syscall` | Process management, signals, setrlimit |\n| `k8s.io/klog/v2` | Structured logging |\n| `time` | Duration and timeout handling |\n| `io` | Stream interfaces |\n| `os` | File operations, process signals |\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Checklist\n\n- [ ] `pkg/picod/picod.go` вҖ” PicoD struct, New(), functional options\n- [ ] `pkg/picod/limits.go` вҖ” ResourceLimits with Validate()\n- [ ] `pkg/picod/security.go` вҖ” SecurityOptions, validation functions\n- [ ] `pkg/picod/executor.go` вҖ” Run(), Start(), Process struct\n- [ ] `pkg/picod/output.go` вҖ” OutputHandler, RunWithStreaming()\n- [ ] `pkg/picod/errors.go` вҖ” ExecutionError types\n- [ ] `pkg/picod/picod_test.go` вҖ” Unit tests for all 15 requirements\n- [ ] All environment variables supported\n- [ ] Resource limits enforced (timeout, memory, CPU, processes)\n- [ ] Security validations prevent path traversal and unauthorized commands\n- [ ] Context cancellation supported\n- [ ] Streaming output supported\n- [ ] klog logging integrated\n- [ ] Code coverage >= 80%\n","after":"# Delta Specification вҖ” AR-019: CLI дәҢиҝӣеҲ¶е…ҘеҸЈ (4 binaries)\n\n## Overview\n\n**Module:** `cmd`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** M  \n**Type:** New feature вҖ” CLI binaries for agentcube Kubernetes resources\n\n**Base Specs:** deployment/client-go.md\n\n---\n\n## Requirements & Scenarios\n\n### REQ-001: PicoD Struct and Initialization\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL provide a `PicoD` struct representing a command execution sandbox with fields: `sandboxID`, `workDir`, `limits`, `securityOpts`, `logger`. The system SHALL provide functional options: `WithWorkDir`, `WithLimits`, `WithSecurityOpts`, `WithLogger`. The system SHALL provide `New(sandboxID string, opts ...Option) *PicoD` constructor.\n\n#### Scenario: New creates PicoD with defaults\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox ID `\"sandbox-123\"`\n- **WHEN** `New(\"sandbox-123\")` is called with no options\n- **THEN** the returned `*PicoD` has `sandboxID = \"sandbox-123\"`, `workDir` from `PICOD_WORKDIR` env (default `/tmp/picod`), `limits` from `DefaultResourceLimits()`, `securityOpts` from `DefaultSecurityOpts()`, `logger` is nil\n\n#### Scenario: WithWorkDir sets working directory\n- **GIVEN** a directory path `\"/custom/workdir\"`\n- **WHEN** `New(\"sandbox-123\", WithWorkDir(\"/custom/workdir\"))` is called\n- **THEN** the returned `*PicoD` has `workDir = \"/custom/workdir\"`\n\n#### Scenario: WithLimits sets resource limits\n- **GIVEN** a `*ResourceLimits` with `Timeout = 60s`\n- **WHEN** `New(\"sandbox-123\", WithLimits(limits))` is called\n- **THEN** the returned `*PicoD` has `limits` set to the provided value\n\n#### Scenario: WithSecurityOpts sets security options\n- **GIVEN** a `*SecurityOptions` with `UID = 1000`\n- **WHEN** `New(\"sandbox-123\", WithSecurityOpts(opts))` is called\n- **THEN** the returned `*PicoD` has `securityOpts` set to the provided value\n\n#### Scenario: WithLogger sets logger\n- **GIVEN** a `klog.Logger` instance\n- **WHEN** `New(\"sandbox-123\", WithLogger(logger))` is called\n- **THEN** the returned `*PicoD` has `logger` set to the provided value\n\n---\n\n### REQ-002: Resource Limits Configuration\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL provide a `ResourceLimits` struct with fields: `Timeout` (time.Duration), `MaxCPU` (float64), `MaxMemory` (int64, bytes), `MaxOutputSize` (int64, bytes), `MaxProcesses` (int). The system SHALL provide `DefaultResourceLimits() *ResourceLimits` returning defaults from environment variables. The system SHALL provide `(l *ResourceLimits) Validate() error`.\n\n#### Scenario: DefaultResourceLimits returns defaults\n- **GIVEN** no environment variables set\n- **WHEN** `DefaultResourceLimits()` is called\n- **THEN** returns `*ResourceLimits` with `Timeout = 30s`, `MaxCPU = 1.0`, `MaxMemory = 128Mi`, `MaxOutputSize = 10MB`, `MaxProcesses = 10`\n\n#### Scenario: DefaultResourceLimits uses environment variables\n- **GIVEN** `PICOD_DEFAULT_TIMEOUT=60s`, `PICOD_MAX_MEMORY=256Mi`, `PICOD_MAX_CPU=2.0`, `PICOD_MAX_OUTPUT_SIZE=20MB`, `PICOD_MAX_PROCESSES=20`\n- **WHEN** `DefaultResourceLimits()` is called\n- **THEN** returns `*ResourceLimits` with values parsed from environment\n\n#### Scenario: Validate accepts valid limits\n- **GIVEN** `ResourceLimits{Timeout: 30s, MaxCPU: 1.0, MaxMemory: 134217728, MaxOutputSize: 10485760, MaxProcesses: 10}`\n- **WHEN** `Validate()` is called\n- **THEN** returns nil (no error)\n\n#### Scenario: Validate rejects zero timeout\n- **GIVEN** `ResourceLimits{Timeout: 0}`\n- **WHEN** `Validate()` is called\n- **THEN** returns error indicating Timeout is required\n\n#### Scenario: Validate rejects negative CPU\n- **GIVEN** `ResourceLimits{MaxCPU: -0.5}`\n- **WHEN** `Validate()` is called\n- **THEN** returns error indicating MaxCPU must be positive\n\n#### Scenario: Validate rejects negative memory\n- **GIVEN** `ResourceLimits{MaxMemory: -100}`\n- **WHEN** `Validate()` is called\n- **THEN** returns error indicating MaxMemory must be positive\n\n#### Scenario: Validate rejects zero output size\n- **GIVEN** `ResourceLimits{MaxOutputSize: 0}`\n- **WHEN** `Validate()` is called\n- **THEN** returns error indicating MaxOutputSize is required\n\n#### Scenario: Validate rejects zero max processes\n- **GIVEN** `ResourceLimits{MaxProcesses: 0}`\n- **WHEN** `Validate()` is called\n- **THEN** returns error indicating MaxProcesses is required\n\n---\n\n### REQ-003: Security Options Configuration\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL provide a `SecurityOptions` struct with fields: `UID` (int), `GID` (int), `Capabilities` ([]string), `ReadOnlyFS` (bool), `NoNetwork` (bool), `AllowedCommands` ([]string). The system SHALL provide `DefaultSecurityOpts() *SecurityOptions`. The system SHALL provide `(o *SecurityOptions) Validate() error`.\n\n#### Scenario: DefaultSecurityOpts returns defaults\n- **GIVEN** no special configuration\n- **WHEN** `DefaultSecurityOpts()` is called\n- **THEN** returns `*SecurityOptions` with `UID = -1` (unchanged), `GID = -1`, `Capabilities = nil`, `ReadOnlyFS = false`, `NoNetwork = false`, `AllowedCommands = nil`\n\n#### Scenario: Validate accepts valid options\n- **GIVEN** `SecurityOptions{UID: 1000, GID: 1000}`\n- **WHEN** `Validate()` is called\n- **THEN** returns nil (no error)\n\n#### Scenario: Validate rejects negative UID (except -1)\n- **GIVEN** `SecurityOptions{UID: -5}`\n- **WHEN** `Validate()` is called\n- **THEN** returns error indicating UID must be >= -1\n\n#### Scenario: Validate rejects negative GID (except -1)\n- **GIVEN** `SecurityOptions{GID: -5}`\n- **WHEN** `Validate()` is called\n- **THEN** returns error indicating GID must be >= -1\n\n#### Scenario: Validate accepts -1 UID (unchanged)\n- **GIVEN** `SecurityOptions{UID: -1}`\n- **WHEN** `Validate()` is called\n- **THEN** returns nil (no error, indicates no UID change)\n\n---\n\n### REQ-004: Command Structure\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL provide a `Command` struct with fields: `Path` (string), `Args` ([]string), `Env` ([]string), `Dir` (string), `Stdin` (io.Reader), `Stdout` (io.Writer), `Stderr` (io.Writer). If `Stdout` or `Stderr` is nil, output SHALL be captured internally.\n\n#### Scenario: Command with all fields\n- **GIVEN** a command with `Path = \"/bin/echo\"`, `Args = []string{\"echo\", \"hello\"}`, `Env = []string{\"FOO=bar\"}`\n- **WHEN** the command is executed\n- **THEN** the command runs with specified path, args, and environment\n\n#### Scenario: Command with nil stdout captures output\n- **GIVEN** a command with `Stdout = nil`\n- **WHEN** the command is executed\n- **THEN** stdout is captured in `CommandResult.Stdout`\n\n#### Scenario: Command with custom stdout uses provided writer\n- **GIVEN** a command with `Stdout = &bytes.Buffer{}`\n- **WHEN** the command is executed\n- **THEN** stdout is written to the provided buffer\n\n---\n\n### REQ-005: CommandResult Structure\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL provide a `CommandResult` struct with fields: `ExitCode` (int), `Stdout` ([]byte), `Stderr` ([]byte), `Duration` (time.Duration), `OOMKilled` (bool), `Timeout` (bool).\n\n#### Scenario: Successful command result\n- **GIVEN** a command that exits with code 0\n- **WHEN** the command completes\n- **THEN** `CommandResult` has `ExitCode = 0`, `Stdout` contains output, `Timeout = false`, `OOMKilled = false`\n\n#### Scenario: Failed command result\n- **GIVEN** a command that exits with code 1\n- **WHEN** the command completes\n- **THEN** `CommandResult` has `ExitCode = 1`, `Stderr` contains error output\n\n#### Scenario: Timeout result\n- **GIVEN** a command that exceeds timeout\n- **WHEN** the command is terminated\n- **THEN** `CommandResult` has `Timeout = true`, `ExitCode = -1` (or appropriate signal code)\n\n#### Scenario: OOM killed result\n- **GIVEN** a command that exceeds memory limit\n- **WHEN** the command is killed\n- **THEN** `CommandResult` has `OOMKilled = true`, `ExitCode` indicates signal\n\n---\n\n### REQ-006: Run Method\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL provide `(p *PicoD) Run(ctx context.Context, cmd *Command) (*CommandResult, error)`. The method SHALL execute the command, wait for completion, apply resource limits, capture output, and return result. The method SHALL respect context cancellation.\n\n#### Scenario: Run executes simple command\n- **GIVEN** a PicoD instance and `Command{Path: \"/bin/echo\", Args: []string{\"echo\", \"hello\"}}`\n- **WHEN** `Run(ctx, cmd)` is called\n- **THEN** command executes, returns `*CommandResult` with `Stdout = []byte(\"hello\\n\")`, `ExitCode = 0`\n\n#### Scenario: Run captures stderr\n- **GIVEN** a command that writes to stderr (`/bin/ls /nonexistent`)\n- **WHEN** `Run(ctx, cmd)` is called\n- **THEN** `CommandResult.Stderr` contains error message, `ExitCode != 0`\n\n#### Scenario: Run respects context cancellation\n- **GIVEN** a long-running command and a context that is cancelled after 1s\n- **WHEN** `Run(ctx, cmd)` is called\n- **THEN** command is terminated, returns error with type `ExecutionErrorCancelled`\n\n#### Scenario: Run enforces timeout\n- **GIVEN** a command and `limits.Timeout = 5s`, command takes 10s\n- **WHEN** `Run(ctx, cmd)` is called\n- **THEN** command is terminated after 5s, returns error with type `ExecutionErrorTimeout`\n\n#### Scenario: Run returns nil error on success\n- **GIVEN** a valid command that completes successfully\n- **WHEN** `Run(ctx, cmd)` is called\n- **THEN** error is nil\n\n---\n\n### REQ-007: Start Method and Process Management\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL provide `(p *PicoD) Start(ctx context.Context, cmd *Command) (*Process, error)`. The system SHALL provide a `Process` struct with fields: `PID` (int), methods `Wait() (*CommandResult, error)` and `Kill(signal os.Signal) error`.\n\n#### Scenario: Start launches background process\n- **GIVEN** a PicoD instance and a long-running command\n- **WHEN** `Start(ctx, cmd)` is called\n- **THEN** returns `*Process` with `PID > 0`, command runs in background\n\n#### Scenario: Process.Wait waits for completion\n- **GIVEN** a `*Process` from `Start()`\n- **WHEN** `process.Wait()` is called\n- **THEN** blocks until command completes, returns `*CommandResult`\n\n#### Scenario: Process.Kill terminates process\n- **GIVEN** a running `*Process`\n- **WHEN** `process.Kill(os.Kill)` is called\n- **THEN** process is terminated, subsequent `Wait()` returns error\n\n#### Scenario: Process.Kill with SIGTERM\n- **GIVEN** a running `*Process`\n- **WHEN** `process.Kill(syscall.SIGTERM)` is called\n- **THEN** process receives SIGTERM and can handle gracefully\n\n---\n\n### REQ-008: Output Streaming\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL provide an `OutputHandler` interface with methods: `OnStdout(data []byte)`, `OnStderr(data []byte)`, `OnComplete(result *CommandResult)`. The system SHALL provide `(p *PicoD) RunWithStreaming(ctx context.Context, cmd *Command, handler OutputHandler) (*CommandResult, error)`.\n\n#### Scenario: RunWithStreaming streams stdout\n- **GIVEN** a command that produces output and an `OutputHandler` implementation\n- **WHEN** `RunWithStreaming(ctx, cmd, handler)` is called\n- **THEN** `OnStdout` is called incrementally as output is produced\n\n#### Scenario: RunWithStreaming streams stderr\n- **GIVEN** a command that writes to stderr\n- **WHEN** `RunWithStreaming(ctx, cmd, handler)` is called\n- **THEN** `OnStderr` is called with error output\n\n#### Scenario: RunWithStreaming calls OnComplete\n- **GIVEN** a command that completes\n- **WHEN** `RunWithStreaming(ctx, cmd, handler)` completes\n- **THEN** `OnComplete(result)` is called with final result\n\n#### Scenario: RunWithStreaming respects output size limit\n- **GIVEN** a command producing output exceeding `MaxOutputSize`\n- **WHEN** `RunWithStreaming(ctx, cmd, handler)` is called\n- **THEN** streaming stops at limit, returns error with type `ExecutionErrorResource`\n\n---\n\n### REQ-009: Command Validation\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL provide `ValidateCommand(cmd *Command, opts *SecurityOptions) error`. The system SHALL provide `IsPathSafe(path, workDir string) bool`. Commands SHALL be validated before execution.\n\n#### Scenario: ValidateCommand accepts valid command\n- **GIVEN** a command with absolute path within workDir\n- **WHEN** `ValidateCommand(cmd, opts)` is called\n- **THEN** returns nil (no error)\n\n#### Scenario: ValidateCommand rejects path traversal\n- **GIVEN** a command with `Path = \"../../../etc/passwd\"`\n- **WHEN** `ValidateCommand(cmd, opts)` is called\n- **THEN** returns error with type `ExecutionErrorSecurity`\n\n#### Scenario: IsPathSafe returns true for safe path\n- **GIVEN** `path = \"/workspace/subdir/file.txt\"`, `workDir = \"/workspace\"`\n- **WHEN** `IsPathSafe(path, workDir)` is called\n- **THEN** returns true\n\n#### Scenario: IsPathSafe returns false for path traversal\n- **GIVEN** `path = \"/workspace/../etc/passwd\"`, `workDir = \"/workspace\"`\n- **WHEN** `IsPathSafe(path, workDir)` is called\n- **THEN** returns false\n\n#### Scenario: ValidateCommand enforces allowlist\n- **GIVEN** `SecurityOptions{AllowedCommands: []string{\"/bin/echo\"}}` and `Command{Path: \"/bin/ls\"}`\n- **WHEN** `ValidateCommand(cmd, opts)` is called\n- **THEN** returns error with type `ExecutionErrorSecurity`\n\n---\n\n### REQ-010: Privilege Dropping\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL provide `DropPrivileges(uid, gid int) error`. When `UID`/`GID` are set in `SecurityOptions`, the system SHALL drop privileges before executing commands.\n\n#### Scenario: DropPrivileges changes UID/GID\n- **GIVEN** running as root, `uid = 1000`, `gid = 1000`\n- **WHEN** `DropPrivileges(1000, 1000)` is called\n- **THEN** process runs with specified UID/GID\n\n#### Scenario: DropPrivileges fails when not root\n- **GIVEN** running as non-root user\n- **WHEN** `DropPrivileges(0, 0)` is called (trying to become root)\n- **THEN** returns error (operation not permitted)\n\n---\n\n### REQ-011: Resource Limit Enforcement\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL provide `SetResourceLimits(limits *ResourceLimits) error`. The system SHALL enforce CPU, memory, and process limits using OS primitives (setrlimit, cgroups, or platform-specific APIs).\n\n#### Scenario: SetResourceLimits sets memory limit\n- **GIVEN** `ResourceLimits{MaxMemory: 134217728}`\n- **WHEN** `SetResourceLimits(limits)` is called\n- **THEN** process memory is limited to 128Mi (via setrlimit or cgroup)\n\n#### Scenario: SetResourceLimits sets process limit\n- **GIVEN** `ResourceLimits{MaxProcesses: 5}`\n- **WHEN** `SetResourceLimits(limits)` is called\n- **THEN** process cannot spawn more than 5 child processes\n\n#### Scenario: Memory limit enforced\n- **GIVEN** a command with `MaxMemory = 10Mi` that tries to allocate 20Mi\n- **WHEN** command executes\n- **THEN** process is killed, `CommandResult.OOMKilled = true`\n\n---\n\n### REQ-012: ExecutionError Types\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL provide `ExecutionError` struct with fields: `Type` (ExecutionErrorType), `Message` (string), `Underlying` (error). The system SHALL define error types: `ExecutionErrorTimeout`, `ExecutionErrorOOM`, `ExecutionErrorCancelled`, `ExecutionErrorSecurity`, `ExecutionErrorResource`, `ExecutionErrorExec`.\n\n#### Scenario: Timeout error type\n- **GIVEN** a command that times out\n- **WHEN** error is returned\n- **THEN** error type is `ExecutionErrorTimeout`\n\n#### Scenario: OOM error type\n- **GIVEN** a command that exceeds memory limit\n- **WHEN** error is returned\n- **THEN** error type is `ExecutionErrorOOM`\n\n#### Scenario: Cancelled error type\n- **GIVEN** a cancelled context\n- **WHEN** `Run(ctx, cmd)` returns error\n- **THEN** error type is `ExecutionErrorCancelled`\n\n#### Scenario: Security error type\n- **GIVEN** a command failing security validation\n- **WHEN** error is returned\n- **THEN** error type is `ExecutionErrorSecurity`\n\n#### Scenario: Exec error type\n- **GIVEN** a command with non-existent path\n- **WHEN** `Run(ctx, cmd)` is called\n- **THEN** error type is `ExecutionErrorExec`\n\n---\n\n### REQ-013: Environment Variables\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL support environment variables for configuration: `PICOD_WORKDIR`, `PICOD_DEFAULT_TIMEOUT`, `PICOD_MAX_MEMORY`, `PICOD_MAX_CPU`, `PICOD_MAX_OUTPUT_SIZE`, `PICOD_MAX_PROCESSES`.\n\n#### Scenario: PICOD_WORKDIR sets default workdir\n- **GIVEN** `PICOD_WORKDIR=/custom/picod`\n- **WHEN** `New(\"sandbox-123\")` is called without `WithWorkDir`\n- **THEN** `PicoD.workDir = \"/custom/picod\"`\n\n#### Scenario: PICOD_DEFAULT_TIMEOUT sets timeout\n- **GIVEN** `PICOD_DEFAULT_TIMEOUT=120s`\n- **WHEN** `DefaultResourceLimits()` is called\n- **THEN** `ResourceLimits.Timeout = 120s`\n\n#### Scenario: PICOD_MAX_MEMORY with unit suffix\n- **GIVEN** `PICOD_MAX_MEMORY=512Mi`\n- **WHEN** `DefaultResourceLimits()` is called\n- **THEN** `ResourceLimits.MaxMemory = 536870912` (512 * 1024 * 1024)\n\n#### Scenario: PICOD_MAX_CPU accepts float\n- **GIVEN** `PICOD_MAX_CPU=0.5`\n- **WHEN** `DefaultResourceLimits()` is called\n- **THEN** `ResourceLimits.MaxCPU = 0.5`\n\n#### Scenario: Default values when env not set\n- **GIVEN** no `PICOD_*` environment variables set\n- **WHEN** `DefaultResourceLimits()` is called\n- **THEN** returns hardcoded defaults (30s timeout, 1.0 CPU, 128Mi memory, 10MB output, 10 processes)\n\n---\n\n### REQ-014: Logging\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL use `klog.Logger` for structured logging. The system SHALL log command start, completion, timeout, cancellation, and errors.\n\n#### Scenario: Run logs command start\n- **GIVEN** a PicoD instance with a logger\n- **WHEN** `Run(ctx, cmd)` is called\n- **THEN** log entry contains \"command_start\", command path, sandbox ID\n\n#### Scenario: Run logs command completion\n- **GIVEN** a command that completes\n- **WHEN** `Run(ctx, cmd)` completes\n- **THEN** log entry contains \"command_complete\", exit code, duration\n\n#### Scenario: Run logs timeout\n- **GIVEN** a command that times out\n- **WHEN** `Run(ctx, cmd)` times out\n- **THEN** log entry contains \"command_timeout\", duration, command path\n\n---\n\n### REQ-015: File Structure\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL provide files: `pkg/picod/picod.go` (PicoD struct, New, options), `pkg/picod/limits.go` (ResourceLimits), `pkg/picod/security.go` (SecurityOptions, validation), `pkg/picod/executor.go` (Run, Start, Process), `pkg/picod/output.go` (OutputHandler, streaming), `pkg/picod/errors.go` (ExecutionError types).\n\n#### Scenario: Package structure\n- **GIVEN** the `pkg/picod` package\n- **WHEN** compiled\n- **THEN** all required files are present and export required types/functions\n\n---\n\n## Data Types\n\n```go\n// PicoD represents a command execution sandbox\ntype PicoD struct {\n    sandboxID    string\n    workDir      string\n    limits       *ResourceLimits\n    securityOpts *SecurityOptions\n    logger       klog.Logger\n}\n\n// ResourceLimits defines execution resource limits\ntype ResourceLimits struct {\n    Timeout       time.Duration\n    MaxCPU        float64\n    MaxMemory     int64\n    MaxOutputSize int64\n    MaxProcesses  int\n}\n\n// SecurityOptions defines security settings\ntype SecurityOptions struct {\n    UID             int\n    GID             int\n    Capabilities    []string\n    ReadOnlyFS      bool\n    NoNetwork       bool\n    AllowedCommands []string\n}\n\n// Command represents a command to execute\ntype Command struct {\n    Path   string\n    Args   []string\n    Env    []string\n    Dir    string\n    Stdin  io.Reader\n    Stdout io.Writer\n    Stderr io.Writer\n}\n\n// CommandResult represents execution result\ntype CommandResult struct {\n    ExitCode  int\n    Stdout    []byte\n    Stderr    []byte\n    Duration  time.Duration\n    OOMKilled bool\n    Timeout   bool\n}\n\n// Process represents a running process\ntype Process struct {\n    PID int\n}\n\n// ExecutionError represents an execution error\ntype ExecutionError struct {\n    Type       ExecutionErrorType\n    Message    string\n    Underlying error\n}\n\ntype ExecutionErrorType string\n\nconst (\n    ExecutionErrorTimeout   ExecutionErrorType = \"timeout\"\n    ExecutionErrorOOM       ExecutionErrorType = \"oom\"\n    ExecutionErrorCancelled ExecutionErrorType = \"cancelled\"\n    ExecutionErrorSecurity  ExecutionErrorType = \"security\"\n    ExecutionErrorResource  ExecutionErrorType = \"resource\"\n    ExecutionErrorExec      ExecutionErrorType = \"exec\"\n)\n```\n\n---\n\n## Environment Variables\n\n| Variable | Required | Default | Notes |\n|----------|----------|---------|-------|\n| `PICOD_WORKDIR` | No | `/tmp/picod` | Base working directory |\n| `PICOD_DEFAULT_TIMEOUT` | No | `30s` | Default command timeout |\n| `PICOD_MAX_MEMORY` | No | `128Mi` | Default memory limit |\n| `PICOD_MAX_CPU` | No | `1.0` | Default CPU limit |\n| `PICOD_MAX_OUTPUT_SIZE` | No | `10MB` | Default output size limit |\n| `PICOD_MAX_PROCESSES` | No | `10` | Default process limit |\n\n---\n\n## File Structure\n\n```\npkg/picod/\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ picod.go          # PicoD struct, New(), functional options\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ limits.go         # ResourceLimits, DefaultResourceLimits(), Validate()\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ security.go       # SecurityOptions, ValidateCommand(), IsPathSafe(), DropPrivileges()\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ executor.go       # Run(), Start(), Process, Command, CommandResult\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ output.go         # OutputHandler, RunWithStreaming()\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ errors.go         # ExecutionError, ExecutionErrorType\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ picod_test.go     # Unit tests\nв””в”Җв”Җ doc.go            # Package documentation\n```\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n| Package | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|\n| `context` | Command cancellation and timeouts |\n| `os/exec` | Command execution primitives |\n| `syscall` | Process management, signals, setrlimit |\n| `k8s.io/klog/v2` | Structured logging |\n| `time` | Duration and timeout handling |\n| `io` | Stream interfaces |\n| `os` | File operations, process signals |\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Checklist\n\n- [ ] `pkg/picod/picod.go` вҖ” PicoD struct, New(), functional options\n- [ ] `pkg/picod/limits.go` вҖ” ResourceLimits with Validate()\n- [ ] `pkg/picod/security.go` вҖ” SecurityOptions, validation functions\n- [ ] `pkg/picod/executor.go` вҖ” Run(), Start(), Process struct\n- [ ] `pkg/picod/output.go` вҖ” OutputHandler, RunWithStreaming()\n- [ ] `pkg/picod/errors.go` вҖ” ExecutionError types\n- [ ] `pkg/picod/picod_test.go` вҖ” Unit tests for all 15 requirements\n- [ ] All environment variables supported\n- [ ] Resource limits enforced (timeout, memory, CPU, processes)\n- [ ] Security validations prevent path traversal and unauthorized commands\n- [ ] Context cancellation supported\n- [ ] Streaming output supported\n- [ ] klog logging integrated\n- [ ] Code coverage >= 80%\n","additions":5,"deletions":3},"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775863740431,"end":1775863740449}}}}
